identificationModule.briefTitle: Thrombolysis Treated With TNK-tPA in Acute Ischemic Stroke Patients （3T Stroke-Ⅲ）
identificationModule.officialTitle: Thrombolysis Treated by TNK-tPA in Acute Ischemic Stroke Patients: a Multi-center, Block Randomized, Positive Drug Parallel Control and Non-inferior Phase Ⅲ Trial, 3T Stroke-Ⅲ

responsibleParty.investigatorTitle: President of Beijing Tiantan Hospital, Capital Medical University, Director of Neurology Center

collaborators.name: Jiangsu FENG HUA Biotech Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd

descriptionModule.briefSummary: The trial is prospective, randomized, open-label, blinded endpoint (PROBE) design. Patients with acute ischemic stroke, who are eligible for standard intravenous thrombolysis within 4.5 hours of stroke onset will be randomized 1:1 to 0.25mg/kg or 0.9 mg/kg alteplase before all participants undergo endovascular thrombectomy.
descriptionModule.detailedDescription: The study will be a multi-center, prospective, randomized, open- label, blinded endpoint (PROBE), controlled phase 3 trial (2 arm with 1:1 randomization) in ischemic stroke patients. Imagine is performed with CT or MRI acutely with imaging follow-up at 24-36 hours. The sample size is 1630.

keywords: TNK-tPA, rt-PA, Acute stroke, phase Ⅲ trial

armGroups.label: Alteplase
armGroups.description: Patients will receive intravenous Alteplase at the standard licensed dose of 0.9 mg/kg up to a maximum of 90mg, 10% as bolus and the remainder over 1 hour.

armGroups.label: Tenecteplase
armGroups.description: Patients will receive intravenous Tenecteplase, 0.25mg/kg, maximum 25mg, administered as a bolus over 5\~10 seconds

primaryOutcomes.description: Proportion of subjects with mRS scores of (0-1) at 90±7 days.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: National Institutes of Health Stroke Scale (NIHSS)
National Institutes of Health Stroke Scale (NIHSS)
secondaryOutcomes.description: Proportion of subjects with ≥ 4 point reduction in NIHSS or reaching 0-1 at 7 ± 2 days or before discharge (whichever occurs first)
Proportion of subjects with mRS scores of (0-2) at 90±7 days.

Incidence of the new vascular events, ischemic stroke, hemorrhagic stroke, myocardial infarction and cardio-cerebral revascularization at 90±7 days. (including: carotid endarterectomy, intracranial and extracranial artery interventional therapy, intracranial and extracranial artery bypass surgery, coronary interventional or bypass therapy)

otherOutcomes.description: Incidence of symptomatic intracranial hemorrhage (sICH) within 24\~36 hours.( According to ECASS Ⅲ and SITS-MOST)

otherOutcomes.measure: Parenchymal hematoma intracranial hemorrhage (type PH2, SITS-MOST)
otherOutcomes.description: Incidence of intracranial hemorrhage (type PH2, SITS-MOST) within 24\~36 hours.
Incidence of any intracranial hemorrhage within 24\~36 hours.
Incidence of Systematic bleeding within 36 hours. (defined by GUSTO)
Vascular mortality at 90±7 days (mainly due to stroke, myocardial infarction or pulmonary embolism)
Mortality due to any cause at 90±7days.
Incidence of severe adverse events(SAEs) at 90±7 days.
Incidence of adverse events(AEs) at 90±7 days.
